# website.shopgrid — Marketing Website

## Project Overview

This is the **public-facing marketing website** for ShopGrid — built with Next.js 15. It includes landing pages, feature highlights, pricing, blog, and contact pages. Fully internationalized (en, ru, uz) using dynamic `[lang]` route segments.

## Tech Stack

- **Framework:** Next.js 15 with App Router and Turbopack (`next dev --turbopack`)
- **Runtime:** React 19, TypeScript
- **Styling:** Tailwind CSS v4 (via `@tailwindcss/postcss`, PostCSS pipeline)
- **i18n:** Lingui v5 with `@lingui/swc-plugin` for Next.js integration
- **Locale Detection:** `negotiator` package in middleware for Accept-Language header parsing
- **Package Manager:** yarn

## Project Structure

```
src/
├── app/
│   ├── [lang]/                  # i18n dynamic route segment
│   │   ├── layout.tsx           # Root layout with Navigation, Footer, LinguiClientProvider
│   │   ├── page.tsx             # Landing page
│   │   ├── LinguiClientProvider.tsx  # Client-side Lingui provider
│   │   ├── components/          # Shared components (Navigation, Footer, LanguageSwitcher, FloatingTelegramButton)
│   │   ├── blog/                # Blog listing + [id] dynamic detail pages
│   │   ├── contact/             # Contact page
│   │   ├── features/            # Features page
│   │   └── pricing/             # Pricing page
│   ├── appRouterI18n.ts         # Server-side i18n instance setup
│   ├── initLingui.ts            # Lingui initialization helper
│   ├── globals.css              # Global Tailwind styles
│   └── favicon.ico
├── data/
│   └── blogPosts.ts             # Blog post data
└── middleware.ts                 # Locale detection/redirect middleware
locales/                         # Lingui message catalogs (en, ru, uz)
lingui.config.ts                 # Lingui configuration
```

## Architecture Patterns

### Internationalization (i18n)
- **Route-based:** All pages under `src/app/[lang]/` receive the locale param
- **Server-side:** `getI18nInstance(lang)` and `initLingui(lang)` used in layouts/pages for SSR
- **Client-side:** `LinguiClientProvider` hydrates the client with the correct locale and messages
- **Middleware:** `src/middleware.ts` detects browser locale via `negotiator` and redirects to `/{lang}/` prefix
- **Static generation:** `generateStaticParams()` generates pages for all locales (en, ru, uz)
- **Catalog management:** Run `yarn po` to extract and compile translations

### Rendering Strategy
- Primarily **static (SSG)** with `generateStaticParams` for locale variants
- Server Components by default; `"use client"` only where needed (LinguiClientProvider, interactive components)
- Metadata generated server-side with `generateMetadata` for SEO

### Layout Composition
Root layout (`[lang]/layout.tsx`) wraps all pages:
`html > body > LinguiClientProvider > Navigation + {children} + Footer + FloatingTelegramButton`

## Coding Standards

- **App Router:** Use Next.js App Router conventions — `page.tsx`, `layout.tsx`, `loading.tsx`, `error.tsx`
- **Server Components first:** Default to Server Components; add `"use client"` only for interactivity
- **Imports:** Use `@/` path alias (maps to `src/`)
- **Styling:** Tailwind utility classes; global styles in `globals.css`
- **i18n:** All user-facing text must use Lingui `i18n._()` (server) or `<Trans>` / `t` macro (client). After changes, run `yarn po`
- **SEO:** Every page must export `generateMetadata` with localized title, description, and OpenGraph tags
- **Images:** Use `next/image` for optimized image loading
- **Links:** Use `next/link` for client-side navigation; always include `/{lang}/` prefix in paths

## Forbidden Patterns

- DO NOT use Pages Router (`pages/` directory) — this is App Router only
- DO NOT skip locale prefix in links — all internal links must include `/{lang}/`
- DO NOT add `"use client"` to components that don't need browser APIs
- DO NOT hardcode text strings — all user-facing content must go through Lingui
- DO NOT use inline `<style>` tags — Tailwind only
- DO NOT import from `next/router` — use `next/navigation` in App Router
